feature_description: In most cases, concessive semantics ("Although X, Y") is expressed by a combination of a conditional converb and an additive particle. However, some dialects allow for other constuctions as well --- to convey concessive meaning, additive may attach to non-conditional verbforms. Parataxis (i.e. juxtaposition of two finite clauses) is also a frequent strategy to express this semantics.

feature_description: Non-specific indefinite pronouns are derived from WH-pronouns (known to speaker, unknown to hearer). There is variation across the dialect as to (1) which suffixes are attached to WH-pronouns and (2) whether those suffixes attach to WH-pronouns directly or a copula occurs between them. In many cases, the suffix deriving non-specific pronouns is identical with the suffix for counterfactual conditionals (e.g., de/jde). Furthermore, non-specifics may optionally attach an additive particle, but, on this map, the presence of additives is not shown.
stimuli: 2. К тебе всегда кто-нибудь приходит.

There is variation across the dialect as to (1) which suffixes are attached to WH-pronouns and (2) whether those suffixes attach to WH-pronouns directly or a copula occurs between them. In many cases, the suffix deriving non-specific pronouns is identical with the suffix for counterfactual conditionals (e.g., de/jde). Furthermore, non-specifics may optionally attach an additive particle, but, on this map, the presence of additives is not shown.
stimuli: Каждая женщина что-нибудь купила на рынке.

feature_description: Scalar additive semantics ("even X did Y", where X is the least likely element to do Y) is usually expressed by an additive particle. However, in some cases, the additive is required to combine with another element, -kina/-kine, in other to convey scalar additive meaning (and not just additive one).

feature_description: The construction for the expression of free-choice indefinite semantics ("whatever, whoever"). Similarly to non-specific indefinite pronouns, they are derived from WH-pronouns. In some dialects, additive particles may optionally occur in free-choice indefinites, but the presence of additives is not encoded in this dataset and not shown on the map. There is some variation as to which suffixes are attached to WH-pronouns to derive the free-choice series: some dialects attach the suffix -ga (and its phonetic variants), while others attach -ga and -de (and variants). Some other peripheral strategies are also present, including a periphrastic strategy with the wetb "want" ("whatever you want"). Importantly, in some dialects, free-choice indefinites appear to be identical with non-specific indefinites ("someone"); see the map on indefinites accordingly.
stimuli: Расул съест что угодно (он голодный).

In some dialects, additive particles may optionally occur in free-choice indefinites, but the presence of additives is not encoded in this dataset and not shown on the map. There is some variation as to which suffixes are attached to WH-pronouns to derive the free-choice series: some dialects attach the suffix -ga (and its phonetic variants), while others attach -ga and -de (and variants). Some other peripheral strategies are also present, including a periphrastic strategy with the wetb "want" ("whatever you want"). Importantly, in some dialects, free-choice indefinites appear to be identical with non-specific indefinites ("someone"); see the map on indefinites accordingly.
stimuli: Расул съест что угодно (он голодный).
answer: rasula šuwgadexa ilesɨ / rasula ilesɨ suwxa hɨgarijden / rasula šuw hɨgadexa ilesɨ / šuwgade ilesɨ
comment: rasula šuwgadexa ilesɨ / rasula ilesɨ suwxa hɨgarijden («расул съест что он захочет»), но это как будто немного другое; rasula šuw hɨgadexa ilesɨ — говорит, что это значит «то что он захочет» / šuwgade ilesɨ — тоже «что попало»

feature_title: Presence of additive in free-choice indefinite pronouns
feature_description: In some dialects, the additive particle optionally attaches to free-choice indefinite pronouns, while in others it does not.  There is, furthermore, some variation as to whether the additive occurs between the WH-word and the suffix signaling free-choice semantics (thus "inside" the pronoun) or if it occurs after the free-choice suffix (thus "outside" the pronoun).

There is, furthermore, some variation as to whether the additive occurs between the WH-word and the suffix signaling indefiniteness (thus "inside" the pronoun) or if it occurs after the indefinite suffix (thus "outside" the pronoun).
stimuli: 1. К тебе кто-то приходил.
name: наида
